caption.title: Comparison of nucleoproteins similarity among hantavirus.
caption.p: Values express the percentage of similarity of Seoul orthohantavirus nucleoprotein (SHNP) and its predicted epitopes among orthohantaviruses associated to HFRS–Gou (GOUV), Hantaan (HTNV), Amur (AMRV), Dobrava-Belgrade (DOBV) and Puumala (PUUV)—and related to HCPS–Juquitiba genotype (JUQV), Andes (ANDV), Laguna-Negra (LANV) and Sin Nombre virus (SNV). The levels of similarity were classified as intermediary (50%<X<75%; orange cells) and high (75%<X<100%; red cells).
